reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 9, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars A Must-Have Accessory for Organized Car Travel!
reviews.reviewText: Rating: ⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐ (5/5 stars)I recently added the Car Sunglasses Holder to my vehicle, and it has proven to be an invaluable addition to my daily commute. This little gadget has made a big difference in keeping my sunglasses safe, organized, and easily accessible while on the road.First and foremost, installation was a breeze. It securely attaches to my car's sun visor without any fuss. The holder's design is sleek and unobtrusive, blending seamlessly into my car's interior without drawing attention.The practicality of this holder cannot be overstated. I no longer have to fumble around searching for my sunglasses while driving. They are conveniently stored in the holder, ready for use whenever needed. This has improved both my safety and driving experience.The holder itself is well-designed, with a secure grip that ensures my sunglasses stay in place even during sharp turns or sudden stops. I appreciate the peace of mind that comes with knowing my sunglasses won't fall and get damaged.What sets this holder apart is its versatility. It's not limited to just sunglasses; I can also use it to store reading glasses, parking tickets, or even my face mask, keeping these essentials within arm's reach.The quality of materials used in this holder is evident. It feels durable and built to last, with no signs of wear or loosening after months of use.In terms of value for money, the Car Sunglasses Holder is a small investment that pays off every day. It brings order and convenience to my car and ensures that my sunglasses are always at my fingertips when the sun gets bright.In conclusion, the Car Sunglasses Holder is a must-have accessory for anyone who spends time on the road. Its easy installation, practicality, and sturdy design make it an essential addition to my car. I can't imagine driving without it, and I highly recommend it to fellow drivers looking for a simple yet effective way to keep their sunglasses or other essentials organized and accessible.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 8, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Works fine, magnet is quite strong
reviews.reviewText: Very easy to install. The magnet that holds it shut is quite strong and you might want to use two hands to open it with one holding the shade. When used to clip sunglasses, I found that clipping it with the glasses pointed down, ie clasping the handles of the sunglasses with the tab, leaves the glasses hanging more loosely and swinging. The glasses seem more secure when fastened with the lenses facing up to the roof as in the photo. It seems well built and the materials appear sturdy enough for daily use. Overall, I’m happy with this purchase and will keep it.
